Data Analysis of Hulu and Netflix Statistics - Matt Aribowo (Rmarkdown)

X1Netflix_Ratings <- X1Netflix_Ratings %>%
  drop_na(rating) %>%
  drop_na(User_Rating) %>%
  mutate(ratings_combine = case_when(
    rating == "TV-Y" ~ "G",
    rating == "TV-G" ~ "G",
    rating == "TV-Y7-FV" ~ "PG",
    rating == "TV-Y7" ~ "PG",
    rating == "TV-PG" ~ "PG",
    rating == "TV-14" ~ "PG-13",
    rating == "TV-MA" ~ "R",
    rating == "UR" ~ "NR",
    TRUE ~ rating
  )) %>%
  mutate(User_Rating = parse_number(User_Rating))

NetflixYear <- X1Netflix_Ratings %>%
  drop_na(year, ratings_combine) %>%
  filter(ratings_combine != "NR") %>%
  group_by(ratings_combine) %>%
  summarize(meanyear = mean(year), n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n))

NetflixYearAvg <- X1Netflix_Ratings %>%
  drop_na(year, User_Rating) %>%
  filter(year != 1940) %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(meanratingnet = mean(User_Rating), n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n))
rating_bar <- netflix %>%
  group_by(rating) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)

topcountries <- netflix %>%
  drop_na(country1) %>%
  group_by(country1) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)

topgenres <- netflix %>%
  drop_na(genre1) %>%
  group_by(genre1) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)


netflix <- netflix %>%
  mutate(rating_combine = case_when(
    rating == "TV-Y" ~ "G",
    rating == "TV-Y7" ~ "PG",
    rating == "TV-PG" ~ "PG",
    rating == "TV-Y7-FV" ~ "PG",
    rating == "UR" ~ "NR",
    rating == "TV-14" ~ "PG-13",
    rating == "TV-MA" ~ "R",
    rating == "NC-17" ~ "R",
    rating == "TV-G" ~ "G",
    TRUE ~ rating
  ))

topcompany <- HuluData %>%
  group_by(Company) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:7)

HuluData <- HuluData %>%
  mutate(huluratings = case_when(
    `TV Rating` == "TV-Y" ~ "TV-G",
    `TV Rating` == "TV-Y7" ~ "TV-PG",
    `TV Rating` == "TV-Y7-FV" ~ "TV-PG",
    `TV Rating` == "PG" ~ "TV-PG",
    TRUE ~ `TV Rating`
  )) %>%
  drop_na(huluratings)

averagerate <- HuluData %>%
  drop_na(Company, `User Rating`) %>%
  group_by(Company) %>%
  summarize(meanrating = mean(`User Rating`), n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)

genrerate <- HuluData %>%
  drop_na(Genre, `User Rating`) %>%
  group_by(Genre) %>%
  summarize(meanrating = mean(`User Rating`), n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)

topHulugenres <- HuluData %>%
  drop_na(Genre) %>%
  group_by(Genre) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  slice(1:5)

topcompany <- topcompany %>%
  mutate(Company = as_factor(Company)) %>%
  mutate(Company = fct_reorder(Company, n))

topHulugenres <- topHulugenres %>%
  mutate(Genre = as_factor(Genre)) %>%
  mutate(Genre = fct_reorder(Genre, n))

genrerate <- genrerate %>%
  mutate(Genre = as_factor(Genre)) %>%
  mutate(Genre = fct_reorder(Genre, meanrating))

averagerate <- averagerate %>%
  mutate(Company = as_factor(Company)) %>%
  mutate(Company = fct_reorder(Company, meanrating))

newrate <- HuluData %>%
  group_by(huluratings) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  mutate(huluratings = fct_relevel(huluratings, "TV-G", "TV-PG", "TV-14", "TV-MA")) %>%
  filter(huluratings != "Not Rated")
